      • getPosition

        Position getPosition()
        Start position of the token.
        Returns:
        never null

      • getRaw

        String getRaw()
        The raw string recognized by the scanner.

        For example a string token "foo" has the raw value "foo" in contrast it's typed string value will be foo.

        Returns:
        never null

      • getType

        TokenType getType()
        Get the token type class.
        Returns:
        never null

      • asBoolean

        Boolean asBoolean()
        Get the boolean typed value.

        This method throws UnsupportedOperationException if the token's token class is not of type TokenType.BOOLEAN.

        Returns:
        never null

      • asFloat

        Float asFloat()
        Get the float typed value.

        This method throws UnsupportedOperationException if the token's token class is not of type TokenType.FLOAT.

        Returns:
        never null

      • asInteger

        Integer asInteger()
        Get the integer typed value.

        This method throws UnsupportedOperationException if the token's token class is not of type TokenType.INTEGER.

        Returns:
        never null

      • asString

        String asString()
        Get the string typed value.

        This method never throws UnsupportedOperationException. It always calls Object.toString() on the recognized typed value.

        Returns:
        never null
